  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0da7\u0db8 \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2\u0daf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Will the pineapple plantation disappear?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Pineapple businessmen say that pineapple cultivation has reached a state of destruction due to the lack of fertilizers and raw materials required for pineapple cultivation.",
        "Growers and traders point out that due to this, they have to leave the pineapple trade and export and thousands of people are losing their livelihood due to this.",
        "Of the 70 pineapple shops that used to be run in Balummahara and Imbulgoda, less than ten shops are left now.",
        "In this regard, it was revealed that the lack of fertilizers and oils used for pineapple cultivation is the main reason for the fall in yields.",
        "According to the retailers, a kilo of pineapple is priced at 250 to 300 rupees and a pineapple which was sold at a price of 200 rupees has to be sold at a price of more than 700 rupees.",
        "Mr. Asela Seneviratne, a pineapple grower in Gampaha area, as well as businessmen named Deshapriya Dias and Ajith Prasanna of Imbulgoda, stated that due to the current situation, they had to leave the cultivation and sale of pineapples altogether.",
        "Some of the traders said that they have lived from this trade for generations. Some traders have abandoned the sale of pineapples and turned to the vegetable trade.",
        "A spokesman of a company that exported pineapples to several countries on a large scale stated that due to the shortage of pineapples and the increase in prices, the export of pineapples that earned foreign exchange to the country has been completely stopped and the government should take steps to provide solutions to the existing bad situation."
      ],
